

Demonstrations against US President George W. Bush turned violent in the southern Argentine city of Mar Del Plata on Friday when protesters threw rocks at the police and smashed windows of buildings.

The demonstrators, chanting slogans such as "Bush, gets out of Argentina," "Bush is a fascist," set fire on a shop and burned a US flag. Throngs of police fired tear gas at the demonstrators.

Xinhua correspondent saw that a policeman was hit by rocks and was put on an ambulance.

The clash took place only several blocks away from the hotel where the Summit of the Americas is held.

